    "To forecast the demand for charging new EV models with larger battery capacities, A DCFCS dynamic planning approach that considers user behaviour and probabilistic driving patterns was developed by Marjan Gjelaj and colleagues 25.",
    "EVs (electric cars) seem to be a viable option for promoting green transportation and reducing CO2 emissions in urban areas.",
    "It is recommended to have saved charging need and synchronized charging need to lower the peak load from EVs and the expense of the charging infrastructure.",
    "They considered a few configurations, such as synchronized storage feeding demand and charging demand, inside the stochastic planning technique.",
    "To reduce the running costs of the DCFCS and the peak demand for EVs, they have proposed an ideal BES as a replacement strategy."
